var e=`# Content Audit: Eastern Kansas Health Care

## Summary
Eastern Kansas Health Care provides comprehensive recruitment support primarily through detailed program pages for internships and residencies, especially its Pharmacy Residency and Psychology Internship programs. These pages include thorough application guidance such as eligibility requirements, required materials, deadlines, and clear instructions for the application process (e.g., PhORCAS for pharmacy, APPIC for psychology). The site offers contact information for program directors and staff, facilitating direct candidate engagement. Job seekers are directed to USAJOBS and the VA careers page, with a dedicated Human Resources phone contact for inquiries. Cross-linking exists between the main Work With Us landing page and specific opportunity pages for apprenticeships, residencies, and jobs. However, there is minimal direct linking to vacareers.va.gov. The content includes actionable next steps like application deadlines, email contacts, and call-to-action statements to encourage applicants to apply or inquire further.

## Highlights
- **Pharmacy Residency Program** ([link](https://www.va.gov/eastern-kansas-health-care/work-with-us/internships-and-fellowships/pharmacy-residency-program/)) — Comprehensive program details including mission, curriculum, application process with PhORCAS link, eligibility, benefits, and direct contact emails for program directors and residents.
- **Psychology Internship Program** ([link](https://www.va.gov/eastern-kansas-health-care/work-with-us/internships-and-fellowships/psychology-internship-program/)) — Clear accreditation information, application deadlines, match numbers, eligibility criteria, and access to admissions data enabling applicants to assess fit and prepare applications.
- **Apply for a job at the VA Eastern Kansas Healthcare System** ([link](https://www.va.gov/eastern-kansas-health-care/work-with-us/jobs-and-careers/)) — Provides guidance on applying, notes importance of completing online applications, includes a Human Resources contact phone number, and points visitors to USAJOBS and VA careers site.
- **Contact Us (Pharmacy Residency Program)** ([link](https://www.va.gov/eastern-kansas-health-care/work-with-us/internships-and-fellowships/pharmacy-residency-program/)) — Specific email contacts for Residency Program Director and current residents are listed, facilitating easy candidate communication.
- **Work With Us main page** ([link](https://www.va.gov/eastern-kansas-health-care/work-with-us/)) — Provides a good overview of available categories, connects users to jobs, internships, and volunteer opportunities with clear calls to visit detailed pages.

## Gaps & Recommendations
### Job links
Job-related pages generally direct candidates to USAJOBS or the VA careers page but lack embedded, direct, clickable job listings or quick-apply links within the Eastern Kansas Health Care site. Adding more direct links to current job openings on the facility site would aid candidate conversion.
> 💡 **Best example from another facility:** [Apply for a job at the VA Central Arkansas Healthcare System](https://www.va.gov/central-arkansas-health-care/work-with-us/jobs-and-careers/) at central-arkansas-health-care

### vacareers.va.gov links
The content does not include direct links to vacareers.va.gov or explicit references routing candidates to this official VA career platform. Adding direct, prominent links to vacareers.va.gov on jobs and program pages could streamline user navigation toward official career tools.
> 💡 **Best example from another facility:** [Apply for a job at the VA West Palm Beach Healthcare System](https://www.va.gov/west-palm-beach-health-care/work-with-us/jobs-and-careers/) at west-palm-beach-health-care

### Application guidance
While detailed for the pharmacy and psychology programs, other job listings and non-pharmacy training opportunities lack clear application instructions or required documents guidance. Enhancing or standardizing application guidance across all recruitment content would improve candidate readiness.
> 💡 **Best example from another facility:** [To Apply](https://www.va.gov/battle-creek-health-care/work-with-us/internships-and-fellowships/post-baccalaureate-registered-nurse-residency-program/) at batttle-creek-health-care

### Cross-linking
Though the Work With Us landing page links to internships, fellowships, jobs, and volunteer pages, there is limited cross-linking between different program types (e.g., linking pharmacy residency pages to psychology internships or jobs). Improved internal linking between different opportunity types would ease navigation and surface more options to potential candidates.
> 💡 **Best example from another facility:** [How to Apply - Cardiovascular and Pulmonary Physical Therapy Residency Program](https://www.va.gov/cincinnati-health-care/work-with-us/internships-and-fellowships/cardiovascular-and-pulmonary-physical-therapy-residency-program/) at cinciinatti-health-care

### Actionable next steps
Some program pages provide application deadlines and contact information but could benefit from clearer, consistent closing calls to action such as explicit 'Apply Now' buttons, direct links to application portals, or step-by-step next steps summaries to guide candidates seamlessly through the process.
> 💡 **Best example from another facility:** [To Apply](https://www.va.gov/battle-creek-health-care/work-with-us/internships-and-fellowships/post-baccalaureate-registered-nurse-residency-program/) at battle-creek-health-care
`;export{e as default};